==English==

===Pronunciation===
pə-tû(r)'nəl, /pə'tɜː(r)nəl/, /p@"t3:(r)n@l/

===Etymology===

Learned borrowing from Vulgar Latin ''paternalis'', from Classical Latin ''paternus'', from ''pater'' meaning "father."

===Adjective===
'''paternal'''

#pertaining to a [[father]], his genes, his relatives, or his side of a family.
#: ''paternal grandfather''
#fatherly
#received or inherited from someone's father.
#committed by a father
#: ''paternal filicide''

